{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum number of set bits in the product of 2023 and n. This is equivalent to finding the minimum Hamming weight of a multiple of 2023. Since 2023 is not a power of 2, the minimum weight is likely small but requires checking properties of the number 2023.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Analyze the prime factorization of 2023 and determine if it shares any common factors with 2. Specifically, check if 2023 is coprime to 2. Use this to determine if there exists an n such that 2023*n is a power of 2 (which would result in k(n)=1), or if the structure of 2023 forces a higher minimum Hamming weight."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Investigate the minimum Hamming weight of multiples of 2023. Test small values of k (the number of ones) by checking if there exist integers a_1, a_2, ..., a_k such that the sum of 2^(a_i) is divisible by 2023. Specifically, check if k=1 is possible, then k=2, then k=3, etc., using modular arithmetic (2^a mod 2023)."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the results to determine the smallest k for which a sum of k powers of 2 is congruent to 0 modulo 2023. If helper_1 shows 2023 is coprime to 2, then k=1 is impossible. Helper_2 will provide the smallest k that satisfies the modular congruence."
}

